      "markdown": "# MattRiley.work\n\nMonorepo for [mattriley.work](https://mattriley.work) â€” a personal site built with a Go API backend and an Astro frontend.\n\nâ†’ For doc navigation and ownership, see [docs/INDEX.md](docs/INDEX.md).  \nâ†’ For contributor workflow, see [docs/CONTRIBUTING.md](docs/CONTRIBUTING.md).\n\n---\n\n## Quick start\n\n### Full stack (Docker Compose)\n\nStarts the API and Redis. API listens on `:1323`, Redis on `:6379`.\n\n```bash\ndocker compose up --build\n```\n\nSet required env vars in your shell or a `.env` file before running. See [environment variables](#environment-variables) below.  \n`DISCORD_WEBHOOK_URL` is required for `POST /contact` to succeed.\n\n### API only (local)\n\n```bash\ncd services/api\ngo mod tidy && mkdir -p bin && go build -o bin/server .\n./bin/server\n```\n\n### Webclient only (local dev)\n\n```bash\ncd services/webclient\npnpm install\npnpm run dev\n```\n\nDev server starts at `http://localhost:4321`. Set `API_ENDPOINT_URL=http://localhost:1323` in `services/webclient/.env` to connect to a local API. Without it, content sections render graceful fallback messages.\n\n---\n\n## Services\n\n| Service | Language / runtime | Path | Port |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `api` | Go + Echo | `services/api/` | `1323` |\n| `webclient` | Astro + Cloudflare adapter | `services/webclient/` | `4321` (dev only) |\n| `cache` | Redis 8 | Docker only | `6379` |\n\n**Data flow:** webclient â†’ `GET /content/*` â†’ api â†’ Redis (cache-first) â†’ Contentful.\n\nThe api also handles contact form submissions (`POST /contact`), serves aggregate homepage content (`GET /content/homepage`), and proxies Contentful image assets (`GET /content/assets/*`).\n\nSee [docs/ARCHITECTURE.md](docs/ARCHITECTURE.md).\n\n---\n\n## Environment variables\n\nCanonical reference: [docs/ENVIRONMENT.md](docs/ENVIRONMENT.md).\n\n### API\n\n| Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `CONTENTFUL_SPACE_ID` | Yes | `â€”` | Contentful space identifier |\n| `CONTENTFUL_API_KEY` | Yes | `â€”` | Contentful Content Delivery API key |\n| `CONTENTFUL_ABOUT_ME_ID` | Yes | `â€”` | Entry ID for the About Me content entry |\n| `REDIS_HOST` | Yes | `â€”` | Redis address in `host:port` form (e.g. `cache:6379`) |\n| `REDIS_PASSWORD` | No | `\"\"` | Redis auth password; leave empty when Redis has no `requirepass` configured |\n| `HOOK_USER` | Yes | `â€”` | Username for `POST /content/hook` basic auth |\n| `HOOK_PASS` | Yes | `â€”` | Password for `POST /content/hook` basic auth |\n| `DISCORD_WEBHOOK_URL` | Yes | `â€”` | Discord webhook URL for contact form notifications |\n| `SENTRY_DSN` | No | `\"\"` | Sentry DSN; if empty, events are not sent |\n\n### Webclient\n\n| Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `API_ENDPOINT_URL` | No | `â€”` | Base URL for the API (e.g. `http://localhost:1323`). If absent or invalid, all dynamic content sections render graceful fallback messages. |\n\n---\n\n## Command matrix\n\n### API (`services/api`)\n\n| Command | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `go mod tidy` | Sync `go.mod` / `go.sum` |\n| `go test ./...` | Run all tests |\n| `go test ./handler -run TestHealth -v` | Run a single test by name |\n| `go vet ./...` | Static analysis |\n| `mkdir -p bin && go build -o bin/server .` | Build server binary to `bin/server` |\n\n### Webclient (`services/webclient`)\n\n| Command | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `pnpm install` | Install dependencies |\n| `pnpm run dev` | Start local dev server at `localhost:4321` |\n| `pnpm run test` | Run Vitest test suite |\n| `pnpm run lint` | Run oxlint |\n| `pnpm run build` | Type-check (`astro check`) and build to `./dist/` |\n| `pnpm run coverage` | Run tests with coverage report |\n\n**Use `pnpm`, not `npm`.**\n\n### Root\n\n| Command | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `docker compose up --build` | Build and start API + Redis |\n\n### Issue tracking (`bd`)\n\n| Command | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `bd onboard` | Initial setup |\n| `bd ready` | List available issues |\n| `bd show <id>` | View issue details |\n| `bd update <id> --status in_progress` | Claim an issue |\n| `bd close <id>` | Mark an issue complete |\n| `bd sync` | Sync local state with git |\n\n---\n\n## Troubleshooting\n\n### API container exits on startup\n\nStartup failures are typically caused by invalid or missing `CONTENTFUL_SPACE_ID` / `CONTENTFUL_API_KEY` during Contentful client setup.  \n`HOOK_USER` / `HOOK_PASS` and `DISCORD_WEBHOOK_URL` are read on request paths (`/content/hook` and `/contact`), so misconfiguration there causes request-time failures rather than startup failure.\n\n### Webclient shows \"unavailable\" for content sections\n\n`API_ENDPOINT_URL` is not set or the API is unreachable. This is expected when running the webclient without the API. Set `API_ENDPOINT_URL=http://localhost:1323` (with the API running) to render live content.\n\n### Webclient build fails with type errors\n\nRun the Astro type-check separately for detailed output:\n\n```bash\ncd services/webclient\npnpm run astro check\n```\n\n### Redis connection refused\n\nWhen running the API outside Docker, either start a local Redis instance or point `REDIS_HOST` to a running container. With Compose, use `REDIS_HOST=cache:6379`; for local-only development use `REDIS_HOST=localhost:6379`.\n\n### `pnpm run preview` does not work\n\nThe Cloudflare adapter does not support the Astro preview command. To smoke-test built output locally:\n\n```bash\ncd services/webclient/dist && python3 -m http.server 8080\n```\n\n---\n\n## Release automation\n\n- **Conventional Commits required** for changes merged to `main` (e.g. `feat: ...`, `fix: ...`, `docs: ...`). Release Please uses these to determine version bumps and changelogs.\n- **Release Please lifecycle**: merges to `main` open/update a release PR per package; merging that PR creates the GitHub Release(s) and tags.\n- **Tag formats**: `api-vX.Y.Z`, `webclient-vX.Y.Z`.\n- **Required secret**: `RELEASE_PLEASE_TOKEN` â€” a GitHub PAT is required because the default `GITHUB_TOKEN` does not trigger downstream workflows on tag/release events.\n\nFull CI and release workflow details are in [docs/OPERATIONS.md](docs/OPERATIONS.md).\n\n---\n\n## FAQ\n\n### Is this over-engineered?\n\nYes. It is a personal site used to experiment with technologies and architectures. Some choices are deliberate over-engineering.\n\n### Why did you choose X to do Y when Z is clearly better?\n\nThe choice was correct at the time, or was made in order to learn. There are always opinions about the best tool for a job in web development. Choose what is right for you, your team, and the project.\n",
